description:
## Problem
`src/shared/error-handling.ts` exports `handleToolError()` which normalizes unknown thrown values into `MCPError` instances with proper categories. However, tool dispatch files (`src/tools/tokens.ts`, `src/tools/typescript.ts`) do their own inline error handling:

```
catch (err) {
  const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
  return createErrorResponse(message);
}
```

This bypasses the error category system and loses structured error information. When `MCPError` instances with specific categories (NOT_FOUND, VALIDATION, GIT) are thrown by handlers, the tool layer flattens them to a plain string.

## Fix
Replace inline catch blocks in all tool dispatch functions with `handleToolError`:

```
catch (err) {
  const mcpErr = handleToolError(err);
  return createErrorResponse(`[${mcpErr.category}] ${mcpErr.message}`);
}
```

Apply to: `handleTokenCall()`, `handleTypeScriptCall()`, and all future tool dispatch functions.

## Acceptance Criteria
- All tool dispatch catch blocks use `handleToolError` from `shared/error-handling.ts`
- Error responses include the category prefix (e.g. `[NOT_FOUND] Component "foo" not found`)
- Add a test verifying category appears in the error response for NOT_FOUND errors

